	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_72086"><p>Oh, nice, someone who is actually waiting for tote.<nobr> <wbr></nobr>:)</p><p>Now that I know that's the case, I will re-prioritize it to arrive sooner. The short story of my discoveries after the original post is that one shouldn't over-design tote; it mostly needs to be a loop that runs the tests on any changes, and has sensible rules for what constitutes "regression" and "progress". Having it do more (for example the double loop suggested in the original post) tends to be more of an obstacle than an actual help.</p><p>Using tote works<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
		
	
